Run the following 3 workflows sequentially. No follow-up questions — execute each one directly.

## 1. /debo vision

Create the Designbook documentation site vision. Read the project README for context.

Product: Designbook Docs — a documentation site that explains how Designbook works,
with step-by-step guides, embedded videos, and screenshots.

## 2. /debo data-model

Only two page types:

- **Landing Page** — canvas_page, purpose: landing-page
- **Docs Page** — node with:
  - `field_media` (reference, inline, multiple) → media bundles: image, video
  - `field_next_doc` (reference) → canvas_page:docs_page

Remove all other content types (no products, articles, taxonomies, views).

## 3. /debo design-guidelines

- **Design reference:** Stitch — https://stitch.withgoogle.com/projects/5626339350367683412
- **MCP server:** stitch / https://stitch.googleapis.com/mcp
- **Component patterns:**
  - Always use layout components: container, grid, section
  - Section is used in Canvas and provides slots: `column_1`, `column_2`
  - Every page wraps content in container → section → grid hierarchy
- **Naming:** kebab-case

